---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Sexual Health: Myth vs. Fact",
  "description": "Test your knowledge with this interactive quiz debunking common sexual health myths.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "The Nookie Nook"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you get pregnant the first time you have sex?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. If you have unprotected penis-in-vagina sex, there is always a risk of pregnancy, regardless of whether it is the first time or the hundredth time."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do STIs always show symptoms?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. Many common STIs like chlamydia, gonorrhea, and HPV are often completely asymptomatic. This is why routine testing is essential."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you get an STI from a toilet seat?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "It is highly unlikely. STIs are caused by bacteria or viruses that require the warm, moist environment of the human body to survive. They die quickly on cold, hard surfaces."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};
---
<SiteLayout
  site="nookienook"
  title="Sexual Health Myths vs Facts Quiz | The Nookie Nook"
  description="Test your knowledge with our interactive quiz. We debunk common myths about pregnancy, STIs, and anatomy with evidence-based facts."
  canonical="https://thenookienook.com/sexual-health-myths"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Sexual Health: Myth vs. Fact</h1>
      <p>Misinformation is everywhere. Test your knowledge and learn the science-backed truth.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
      <p>Part of our <a href="/sites/nookienook/sexual-health-guide">Comprehensive Sexual Health Guide</a> series.</p>

      <p>From playground rumors to misleading internet forums, sexual health is surrounded by myths. These misconceptions aren't just harmless falsehoods; they can lead to unintended pregnancies, untreated infections, and unnecessary shame. Take our interactive quiz below to see how much you really know.</p>

      <div class="quiz-container" id="quiz-app">
        <div id="quiz-progress" class="quiz-progress">Question 1 of 15</div>

        <div id="quiz-question-container" class="quiz-card">
          <h3 id="quiz-statement" class="quiz-statement">Loading...</h3>
          <div class="quiz-options">
            <button class="quiz-btn myth-btn" onclick="handleAnswer(false)">Myth</button>
            <button class="quiz-btn fact-btn" onclick="handleAnswer(true)">Fact</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div id="quiz-explanation-container" class="quiz-card" style="display: none;">
          <div id="result-badge" class="result-badge"></div>
          <h3 id="explanation-title" class="explanation-title"></h3>
          <p id="explanation-text" class="explanation-text"></p>
          <button class="next-btn" onclick="nextQuestion()">Next Statement</button>
        </div>

        <div id="quiz-results" class="quiz-card" style="display: none; text-align: center;">
          <h2>Quiz Complete!</h2>
          <div class="score-display">You scored <span id="final-score"></span> out of <span id="total-questions"></span></div>
          <p id="score-message" class="score-message"></p>
          <button class="next-btn" onclick="resetQuiz()" style="margin-top: 2rem;">Retake Quiz</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Why Misinformation Spreads</h2>
      <p>Sexual health education is highly variable depending on where you live. Many people receive "abstinence-only" education, which often intentionally omits or misrepresents facts about contraception and STIs. Furthermore, stigma surrounding sex makes people hesitant to ask their doctors for clarification, turning instead to unreliable sources online.</p>
      <p>Empower yourself by seeking out evidence-based information. If you're unsure about something, check resources like the CDC, Planned Parenthood, or consult our <a href="/sites/nookienook/guide-talking-to-doctor">Guide to Talking to Your Doctor</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const questions = [
      {
        statement: "You can't get pregnant the first time you have sex.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "If you have unprotected penis-in-vagina sex, there is always a risk of pregnancy, regardless of whether it is the first time or the hundredth time."
      },
      {
        statement: "You can get an STI from a public toilet seat.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "It is highly unlikely. STIs are caused by bacteria or viruses that require the warm, moist environment of the human body to survive. They die quickly on cold surfaces."
      },
      {
        statement: "The 'pull-out' method is an effective form of birth control.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "The pull-out method is unreliable. Pre-ejaculate (pre-cum) can contain sperm, and it requires perfect timing and self-control, leading to a high typical-use failure rate."
      },
      {
        statement: "Most people with an STI don't know they have one.",
        isFact: true,
        explanation: "Many common STIs, including chlamydia, gonorrhea, and HPV, are frequently asymptomatic. This is why regular testing is vital even if you feel fine."
      },
      {
        statement: "You cannot get pregnant while on your period.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "While less likely, it is possible. Sperm can live inside the body for up to 5 days. If you have a short cycle and ovulate soon after your period ends, sperm from intercourse during your period could fertilize the egg."
      },
      {
        statement: "Two condoms offer double the protection.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "Using two condoms at once causes friction between them, making them much more likely to tear or break. Only use one condom at a time."
      },
      {
        statement: "Birth control pills protect against STIs.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "Hormonal birth control (pills, patches, IUDs) only protects against pregnancy. Only barrier methods like condoms protect against STIs."
      },
      {
        statement: "You can get an STI from oral sex.",
        isFact: true,
        explanation: "Many STIs, including herpes, gonorrhea, syphilis, and HPV, can be transmitted through oral sex. Using dental dams or condoms reduces this risk."
      },
      {
        statement: "Peeing after sex prevents pregnancy.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "Urine comes from the urethra, not the vagina. Peeing after sex is highly recommended to help flush bacteria out of the urethra and prevent UTIs, but it does absolutely nothing to prevent pregnancy."
      },
      {
        statement: "Douching is a healthy way to clean the vagina.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "The vagina is self-cleaning. Douching disrupts the natural balance of healthy bacteria (flora), increasing the risk of infections like bacterial vaginosis and yeast infections."
      },
      {
        statement: "Herpes is incredibly common.",
        isFact: true,
        explanation: "According to the WHO, an estimated 67% of the global population under age 50 has HSV-1 (oral herpes, which can also cause genital herpes), and 13% have HSV-2."
      },
      {
        statement: "Hormonal birth control causes weight gain.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "Extensive studies show no direct link between most birth control pills and long-term weight gain. Some people may experience temporary water retention, but significant weight gain is rare (except potentially with the Depo shot)."
      },
      {
        statement: "You can't get an STI if you only have one partner.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "You can get an STI in a monogamous relationship if one partner contracted an infection previously and it has gone undetected (since many are asymptomatic)."
      },
      {
        statement: "Consent is still required if you are married.",
        isFact: true,
        explanation: "Consent is always required, regardless of relationship status or history. Being in a committed relationship does not grant automatic or permanent access to someone's body."
      },
      {
        statement: "Men cannot do Kegel exercises.",
        isFact: false,
        explanation: "People of all genders have a pelvic floor. Kegel exercises can help men improve bladder control and may even assist with erectile function and ejaculation control."
      }
    ];

    let currentQuestionIndex = 0;
    let score = 0;

    function initQuiz() {
      currentQuestionIndex = 0;
      score = 0;
      updateUI();
    }

    function updateUI() {
      const q = questions[currentQuestionIndex];
      document.getElementById('quiz-progress').innerText = `Question ${currentQuestionIndex + 1} of ${questions.length}`;
      document.getElementById('quiz-statement').innerText = `"${q.statement}"`;

      document.getElementById('quiz-question-container').style.display = 'block';
      document.getElementById('quiz-explanation-container').style.display = 'none';
      document.getElementById('quiz-results').style.display = 'none';
    }

    function handleAnswer(userGuess) {
      const q = questions[currentQuestionIndex];
      const isCorrect = userGuess === q.isFact;

      if (isCorrect) score++;

      const badge = document.getElementById('result-badge');
      if (isCorrect) {
        badge.innerText = "Correct!";
        badge.className = "result-badge correct";
      } else {
        badge.innerText = "Incorrect";
        badge.className = "result-badge incorrect";
      }

      document.getElementById('explanation-title').innerText = q.isFact ? "It's a Fact." : "It's a Myth.";
      document.getElementById('explanation-text').innerText = q.explanation;

      document.getElementById('quiz-question-container').style.display = 'none';
      document.getElementById('quiz-explanation-container').style.display = 'block';
    }

    function nextQuestion() {
      currentQuestionIndex++;
      if (currentQuestionIndex < questions.length) {
        updateUI();
      } else {
        showResults();
      }
    }

    function showResults() {
      document.getElementById('quiz-progress').style.display = 'none';
      document.getElementById('quiz-explanation-container').style.display = 'none';
      document.getElementById('quiz-results').style.display = 'block';

      document.getElementById('final-score').innerText = score;
      document.getElementById('total-questions').innerText = questions.length;

      const messageEl = document.getElementById('score-message');
      const percentage = score / questions.length;

      if (percentage === 1) {
        messageEl.innerText = "Perfect! You have an excellent grasp of evidence-based sexual health.";
      } else if (percentage >= 0.7) {
        messageEl.innerText = "Great job! You know your stuff, but there's always more to learn.";
      } else {
        messageEl.innerText = "Good effort! Sexual health myths are common. Check out our comprehensive guides to learn more.";
      }
    }

    function resetQuiz() {
      document.getElementById('quiz-progress').style.display = 'block';
      initQuiz();
    }

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initQuiz);
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.2rem; }

    .content-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .content-section p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .content-section a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: underline; }
    .content-section a:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }

    .quiz-container { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
    .quiz-progress { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }

    .quiz-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 2rem; }

    .quiz-statement { font-size: 1.5rem; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4; }

    .quiz-options { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) { .quiz-options { flex-direction: column; } }

    .quiz-btn { flex: 1; padding: 1rem 2rem; border: none; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: transform 0.1s, opacity 0.2s; color: #fff; max-width: 250px; }
    .quiz-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; transform: scale(1.02); }
    .quiz-btn:active { transform: scale(0.98); }
    .myth-btn { background-color: #E05A5A; }
    .fact-btn { background-color: #2DB89A; }

    .result-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 0.4rem 1rem; border-radius: 99px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .result-badge.correct { background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.2); color: #2DB89A; border: 1px solid #2DB89A; }
    .result-badge.incorrect { background: rgba(224, 90, 90, 0.2); color: #E05A5A; border: 1px solid #E05A5A; }

    .explanation-title { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .explanation-text { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }

    .next-btn { background: var(--border-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.2s; }
    .next-btn:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-color: var(--text-primary); }

    .score-display { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    #final-score { color: var(--accent-color); font-weight: 800; font-size: 2rem; }
    .score-message { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
